The paper deals with a combination of multiple techniques for 5G communication systems, including multi-user MIMO (cs.IT), cognitive radio (cs.NI), and simultaneous wireless information and power transfer (cs.SY). The focus is on designing an optimal precoder that maximizes the sum-utility cost function for the ID users while satisfying various constraints, which involves optimization (cs.MM) and system design (cs.CR).
